                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.24/12–348</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Peru</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/> No. 297</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-03">December 3,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State transmits herewith for the confidential information and
                    records of the Embassy a copy of the Department’s note <pb facs="0751" n="735" xml:id="pg_735"/> to the Embassy of Peru in Washington<note n="1" xml:id="d519fn1">Not printed.</note> advising the Government of Peru that
                    the statement of the lend-lease account reported in the Department’s note of
                    June 25, 1948, to the Peruvian Embassy<note n="2" xml:id="d519fn2">The balance
                        due on the basis of reportings to May 31, 1948 was $2,882,910.64, according
                        to the note of June 25, not printed (823.24/6–2548).</note> (refer to
                    instruction No. 166 of June 25, 1948<note n="1" xml:id="d519fn3">Not
                        printed.</note>) may now be considered complete and final.</p>
                <p>For the Embassy’s further information there are contingent accounts reported by
                    the Treasury Department as outstanding on October 31, 1948, as follows:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Lend-Lease Pipeline Account</hi>
                </p>
